===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=偀-ancient}}

{{unc|zh}}. There are several possibilities:
* Of {{der|zh|sit|-}} origin, related to {{cog|lus|ân||to open the mouth to receive food, to open to}}, {{m|lus|âng||to open (mouth), to gape with open mouth}}; if so, this word would come from the idea of an open flower ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{cog|lus|êng||light}}, {{m|lus|ên||to shine, to give light, bright, brilliant}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{cog|mkh-ban-pro|*ʔaːŋ||bright}} (from {{cog|mkh-pro|*cʔaiŋ||[[light]], to [[shine]]}}), which may be also/instead related to {{och-l|影|shadow}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{och-l|秧|rice seedling}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 2011}}).

